dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Woodbridge & Felixstowe, solid and drift, sheet 208 and 225
dc_description_s: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 208/225 solid and drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 52.150000. South Decimal Degree 51.9000. East Decimal Degree 1.7167. West Decimal Degree 1.3000. In upper left corner: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain (Sixth edition). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth shown by contour intervals. "Geological survey by W. Whitaker and W. H. Dalton. Published on the Old Series sheets 48 N.E. in 1882. 49 S.W. and 50 S.E. in 1883. Transferred to the New Series sheets 208 and 225 and published 1928. Published as a combined sheet in 1956.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1956.
